@startuml
title Podman Machine - Connectivity Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "CLI" as CLI
participant "Libmachine\nClient" as Client
participant "Filestore" as Store
participant "Host" as Host
participant "Driver\n(VirtualBox/QEMU)" as Driver
participant "RPC\nPlugin" as RPC
participant "Provisioner" as Prov
participant "SSHCommander" as SSH
participant "VM" as VM
participant "Podman\nRemote" as PodmanRemote
participant "Varlink\nBridge" as Varlink
participant "Network\n(NFTables)" as Network

== VM Creation & Network Setup ==
User -> CLI: create command
activate CLI
CLI -> Client: NewHost(driverName, options)
activate Client
Client -> Store: Save host config
activate Store
Store --> Client: config saved
deactivate Store

Client -> Driver: Create(hostOptions)
activate Driver
Driver -> RPC: RPC call to plugin driver
activate RPC
RPC -> VM: Create VM instance
activate VM
VM --> RPC: VM created
deactivate VM
RPC --> Driver: VM created
deactivate RPC

Driver -> Network: Configure host-only network
activate Network
Network --> Driver: Network configured
deactivate Network

Driver -> Network: Setup port forwarding
Network --> Driver: Port forwarding enabled
deactivate Network

Driver --> Client: VM created
deactivate Driver
Client --> CLI: Host created
deactivate Client
CLI --> User: VM created successfully
deactivate CLI

== VM Start & SSH Connection ==
User -> CLI: start command
activate CLI
CLI -> Client: Load(hostName)
activate Client
Client -> Store: Load host config
activate Store
Store --> Client: host config
deactivate Store

Client -> Host: Driver.Start()
activate Host
Host -> Driver: Start()
activate Driver
Driver -> RPC: RPC call to start VM
activate RPC
RPC -> VM: Start VM
activate VM
VM --> RPC: VM started
deactivate VM
RPC --> Driver: Started
deactivate RPC
Driver --> Host: VM running
deactivate Driver

Host -> Prov: Provision(driver, authOptions)
activate Prov
Prov -> SSH: NewSSHCommander(driver)
activate SSH
SSH -> VM: SSH connection (key-based auth)
activate VM
VM --> SSH: SSH session established
SSH --> Prov: SSH commander ready
deactivate SSH

Prov -> SSH: Execute: detect OS
activate SSH
SSH -> VM: Run OS detection commands
VM --> SSH: OS info (Fedora/Boot2Podman)
deactivate VM
SSH --> Prov: OS detected
deactivate SSH

Prov -> SSH: Execute: install Podman
activate SSH
SSH -> VM: Install Podman packages
activate VM
VM --> SSH: Podman installed
deactivate VM
SSH --> Prov: Installation complete
deactivate SSH

Prov -> SSH: Execute: configure Podman engine
activate SSH
SSH -> VM: Apply engine config from template
activate VM
VM --> SSH: Config applied
deactivate VM
SSH --> Prov: Engine configured
deactivate SSH

Prov --> Host: Provisioning complete
deactivate Prov
Host --> Client: VM started and provisioned
deactivate Host
Client --> CLI: Start complete
deactivate Client
CLI --> User: VM started
deactivate CLI

== Environment Configuration & Remote Connection ==
User -> CLI: env command
activate CLI
CLI -> Client: Load(hostName)
activate Client
Client -> Store: Load host config
activate Store
Store --> Client: host config with certs
deactivate Store
Client -> Host: GetURL()
activate Host
Host -> Driver: GetURL()
activate Driver
Driver --> Host: VM endpoint URL
deactivate Driver
Host --> Client: Connection URL
deactivate Host
Client --> CLI: Env variables (PODMAN_HOST, certs)
deactivate Client
CLI --> User: Export connection vars
deactivate CLI

== SSH Direct Access ==
User -> CLI: ssh command
activate CLI
CLI -> Client: Load(hostName)
activate Client
Client -> Store: Load SSH keys
activate Store
Store --> Client: SSH private key
deactivate Store
Client -> Host: Driver.GetSSHHostname()
activate Host
Host -> Driver: GetSSHHostname()
activate Driver
Driver --> Host: VM hostname/IP
deactivate Driver
Host --> Client: SSH endpoint
deactivate Host
Client -> SSH: SSH connection with key
activate SSH
SSH -> VM: Establish SSH session
activate VM
VM --> SSH: Interactive shell
CLI <--> SSH: Tunnel user I/O
SSH <--> VM: Interactive commands
deactivate VM
deactivate SSH
deactivate Host
deactivate Client
deactivate CLI

== Podman Remote Client Communication ==
User -> PodmanRemote: podman-remote command
activate PodmanRemote
PodmanRemote -> SSH: SSH tunnel to VM
activate SSH
SSH -> VM: Establish secure connection
activate VM
VM --> SSH: Connection ready
deactivate VM
SSH --> PodmanRemote: Tunnel established
deactivate SSH

PodmanRemote -> Varlink: Connect via Varlink bridge
activate Varlink
Varlink -> VM: io.podman Varlink interface
activate VM
VM -> Varlink: Podman API response
deactivate VM
Varlink --> PodmanRemote: API data
deactivate Varlink
PodmanRemote --> User: Command result
deactivate PodmanRemote

== Certificate Regeneration & Renewal ==
User -> CLI: regenerate-certs command
activate CLI
CLI -> Client: Load(hostName)
activate Client
Client -> Store: Delete old certificates
activate Store
Store --> Client: Deleted
deactivate Store

Client -> Host: ConfigureAuth()
activate Host
Host -> Driver: GetSSHHostname()
activate Driver
Driver --> Host: VM endpoint
deactivate Driver

Host -> SSH: Connect to VM
activate SSH
SSH -> VM: SSH connection
activate VM
VM --> SSH: Connected
Host -> SSH: Execute: regenerate TLS certs
SSH -> VM: Generate new certificates
VM --> SSH: Certs generated
deactivate VM
SSH --> Host: Certificates ready
deactivate SSH

Host -> Store: Save new certificates
activate Store
Store --> Host: Saved
deactivate Store
Host --> Client: Auth reconfigured
deactivate Host
Client --> CLI: Certs regenerated
deactivate Client
CLI --> User: Certificate renewal complete
deactivate CLI

== Network Port Forwarding Management ==
User -> CLI: Modify port forwarding
activate CLI
CLI -> Client: Load(hostName)
activate Client
Client -> Host: Driver operations
activate Host
Host -> Driver: Update network config
activate Driver
Driver -> Network: Configure NFTables rules
activate Network
Network -> VM: Apply packet filtering
activate VM
VM --> Network: Rules applied
deactivate VM
Network --> Driver: Forwarding updated
deactivate Network
Driver --> Host: Network updated
deactivate Driver
Host --> Client: Complete
deactivate Host
Client --> CLI: Port forwarding configured
deactivate Client
CLI --> User: Network updated
deactivate CLI

== VM Shutdown & Cleanup ==
User -> CLI: stop/rm command
activate CLI
CLI -> Client: Load(hostName)
activate Client
Client -> Host: Driver.Stop()
activate Host
Host -> Driver: Stop()
activate Driver
Driver -> RPC: RPC call to stop VM
activate RPC
RPC -> VM: Stop VM
activate VM
VM --> RPC: VM stopped
deactivate VM
RPC --> Driver: Stopped
deactivate RPC
Driver -> Network: Remove port forwarding
activate Network
Network --> Driver: Rules removed
deactivate Network
Driver --> Host: VM stopped
deactivate Driver

alt Remove VM
    Host -> Driver: Remove()
    activate Driver
    Driver -> RPC: RPC call to remove VM
    activate RPC
    RPC -> VM: Delete VM
    activate VM
    VM --> RPC: VM deleted
    deactivate VM
    RPC --> Driver: Removed
    deactivate RPC
    Driver --> Host: VM removed
    deactivate Driver
    Host -> Store: Delete host config
    activate Store
    Store --> Host: Config deleted
    deactivate Store
end

Host --> Client: Operation complete
deactivate Host
Client --> CLI: Complete
deactivate Client
CLI --> User: VM stopped/removed
deactivate CLI

@enduml
